Under his arm he carried documents with the new three-storey rental contracts: his, his daughter's and his son's, who is serving his sentence.
All three have just caught the liberalization of rents.
Instead of 3,500 Czech crowns a month, the child will pay from next year 4,100 crowns for a two-room apartment with second-class separate kitchen.
"In addition, there is no hot water and heating is based on a solid fuel boiler," the man's finger shows in his son's new contract, about whose signature has full powers.
"But I signed it," explains half angry, half resigned.
