More and more parents use people monitoring devices to control their children
Fear of children leads more and more people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for the monitoring of vehicles, can also follow the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, in case of the disappearance of the nine-year-old Anička Janatková girl.
For the moment the device has the approximate size of a set of bezels, but it will soon be reduced to the size of a watch.
Many people were afraid of the missing Anička case and began to report on the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the expense of invading your privacy.
"We are all trying to tell ourselves that it is not about spying, but another way to reduce the chances of a tragedy," considers Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the suppliers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I recognize that in certain cases such devices can be abused, for example if they get into someone's pocket without their knowledge, but we have not yet met with such cases."
"Most customers actually buy it for security reasons," adds Pilin.
In their view, children should always know what the "cajita" is for and how it is used in the event of an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bočková warns about the fact that if the child does not want to take it, he will just throw it away.
"Even younger children show great creativity when intentionally losing certain things if they want to avoid being controlled."
"Before, parents relied heavily on mobile phones, but these could be turned off as easily as the tracking device," Bočková says.
In your opinion, it is questionable whether in case of attack such a device is really useful.
"If it is a prepared kidnapping, the author will almost always check whether the child wears some kind of electronic device that can reveal his location."
"Now it's the phone."
"As the use of tracking devices is expanding, it will also search for them, as their sale will no doubt be made with much publicity."
"In such cases, criminals always go one step ahead of the police," says the psychologist.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the case of an improvised pedophile attack.
According to Robert Čech of the company RC Monitoring, which provides tracking services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can help.
"The device can be configured to send the position regularly after a certain period."
"If you suffer damage, at least you will facilitate the last position of the person in question."
"The most expensive devices have integrated a tilt meter, so if the person simply slips and remains motionless, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question," says Čech.
In your opinion, a service of this type can be obtained even with smart mobile phones with navigation, in which only special software should be installed.
